"tag":"html:p","attrib":{},"text":" ","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null},{"tag":"html:td","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"html:p","attrib":{},"text":" ","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null},{"tag":"html:td","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"html:p","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"html:a","attrib":{"href":"/us/act/1878-06-18/ch263/s7"},"text":"June 18, 1878, ch. 263, § 7","children":[],"tail":" (less applicability to "},{"tag":"html:a","attrib":{"href":"/us/act/1949-04-16/ch38/s108/a"},"text":"§ 108(a) of the Act of Apr. 16, 1949, ch. 38","children":[],"tail":", as amended), "},{"tag":"html:a","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/20/150"},"text":"20 Stat. 150","children":[],"tail":"."}],"tail":null}],"tail":null}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"html:tr","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"html:td","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"html:p","attrib":{},"text":" ","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null},{"tag":"html:td","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"html:p","attrib":{},"text":" ","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null},{"tag":"html:td","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"html:p","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"html:a","attrib":{"href":"/us/act/1928-05-29/ch902"},"text":"May 29, 1928, ch. 902","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"html:a","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/45/996"},"text":"45 Stat. 996","children":[],"tail":"; "},{"tag":"html:a","attrib":{"href":"/us/act/1938-01-29/ch12/s2"},"text":"Jan. 29, 1938, ch. 12, § 2","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"html:a","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/52/8"},"text":"52 Stat. 8","children":[],"tail":"."}],"tail":null}],"tail":null}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Subsection (a) consolidates the various service computation provisions applicable to voluntary retirement of commissioned officers. Clause (1) is substituted for 10:951. Clause (2) is substituted for 10:951b. The words “pay period and”, in 10:951a, are omitted as superseded by section 202 of the Career Compensation Act of 1949, ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/63/807"},"text":"63 Stat. 807","children":[],"tail":" ("},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t37/s233"},"text":"37 U.S.C. 233","children":[],"tail":"). The words “longevity pay and”, in "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/act/1878-06-18/ch263/s7"},"text":"section 7 of the Act of June 18, 1878, ch. 263","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/20/150"},"text":"20 Stat. 150","children":[],"tail":", are omitted for the same reason. The last sentence of section 7 of that act is omitted, since the distinction between limited and unlimited retired lists was abolished by "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/act/1948-06-29/ch708/s201"},"text":"section 201 of the Act of June 29, 1948, ch. 708","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/62/1084"},"text":"62 Stat. 1084","children":[],"tail":". Clause (3) is inserted, since a person entitled to count service under "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t10/s8683"},"text":"section 8683 of this title","children":[],"tail":" might cease to be a nurse or woman medical specialist and thereafter become entitled to retire under one of the revised sections referred to in subsection (a) of this revised section."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"In subsection (b), the words “as a member of the Medical Reserve Corps”, in 10:953a, are omitted as covered by subsection (a)(1). The words “are computed by adding to his service under subsection (a)” are substituted for the words “shall be credited to the same extent as service under a Regular Army commission”.","children":[],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Subsection (c) is substituted for 10:953a (less 1st sentence).","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"role":"crossHeading","topic":"editorialNotes","id":"idab6d8be5-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"b","attrib":{},"text":"Editorial Notes","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"amendments","id":"idab6d8be6-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Amendments","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"2021—","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/116/283/s923/c/19/B"},"text":"Pub. L. 116–283, § 923(c)(19)(B)","children":[],"tail":", which directed amendment of subsec. (a) by substituting “the officer’s” for “his” wherever appearing, was executed by making the substitution wherever appearing in this section to reflect the probable intent of Congress."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Subsec. (a). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/116/283/s923/c/19/A/i"},"text":"Pub. L. 116–283, § 923(c)(19)(A)(i)","children":[],"tail":", inserted “or the Space Force” after “of the Air Force” in introductory provisions."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Subsec. (a)(1). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/116/283/s923/c/19/A/ii"},"text":"Pub. L. 116–283, § 923(c)(19)(A)(ii)","children":[],"tail":", substituted “, the Air Force, or the Space Force” for “or the Air Force”."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"2018—","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/115/232/s806/b/13"},"text":"Pub. L. 115–232, § 806(b)(13)","children":[],"tail":", renumbered "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t10/s8926"},"text":"section 8926 of this title","children":[],"tail":" as this section."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Subsecs. (a) to (c). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/115/232/s809/a"},"text":"Pub. L. 115–232, § 809(a)","children":[],"tail":", substituted “section 9311, 9318, or 9324” for “section 8911, 8918, or 8924”."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"1996—Subsec. (d). ","childre